way from the skin so it evaporates quickly. This helps reduce irritation that may trigger the onset of the \"itch-scratch\" cycle, and is one reason why the ComfortLuxe sleepwear has been awarded the Seal of Acceptance by the National Eczema Association. For additional comfort, the fabric has flat interior seams to minimize abrasion.</p><h5>Keeps Children Comfortable During Sleep</h5><p>The ComfortLuxe Sensitive Skin Sleepwear\'s lightweight fabric wicks moisture from your little one\'s skin and allows fresh air to circulate. This allows your child to maintain a stable body temperature throughout the night for a more comfortable sleep, regardless of the season.</p><h5>100 Percent Chemical Free for Safety</h5><p>ComfortLuxe is free from chemicals, so its moisture wicking performance benefits will never disappear, even after multiple washings. In addition, this smart fabric won\'t absorb lotions or topical creams on the surface of the skin to help maximize their benefits and promote the healing of skin irritation.</p><h5>About HALO</h5><p>Founded by Bill Schmid after losing his infant daughter to SIDS (Sudden Infant Death Syndrome), HALO is best-known for its SleepSack wearable blanket, which helps your little one sleep safely by replacing loose blankets in the crib. HALO SleepSack products are used by hundreds of hosptials in the U.S., and it is the only wearable blanket to carry gold seals from First Candle/SIDS Alliance and the Canadian Foundation for the Study of Infant Deaths.</p></div><div class=\"break\"></div></div><div style=\"width: 840px; margin: 20px auto; text-align: center;\"><div class=\"centerImage\"><img src=\"http://images.amazon.com/images/G/01/baby/detail-page/c26-B000069EXN-halo-logo.png\" alt=\"Halo SleepSack Logo\"><h5 style=\"color: #055C9F; font-size: 24px; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', \'Lucida Grande\', Verdana, sans-serif;\">HALO Collection</h5></div><div style=\"width: 210px; float: left;\"><img src=\"http://images.amazon.com/images/G/01/b